{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 1 implements these considerations for self-triage decisions.",
    "Based on these considerations, Brunswik coined the term ecological validity and proposed the concept of representative design as a method for sampling ecologically valid stimuli.",
    "Using representative design, stimuli (or vignettes) are sampled directly from situations to which the researcher would like to generalize, thereby trying to maintain the natural correlations between cues and the latent variable 23.",
    "This approach contrasts starkly with the traditional systematic design, where parameters of the stimuli are",
    "Appropriate Self-Triage Level Cues Decision-Maker Cue Utilization Self-Triage Level Decision Cue 1 Cue 2 Cue 3 … #1 #2 #3 The self-triage level that is most appropriate."
  ]
}